2026-04-14 08:18:28,186 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: We have identified the target cell containing the current formula: cell C14 in sheet "AB" with value `=SUM(C2:C13)`. The user wants a formula that sums the range while ignoring any `#NUM!` errors. In LibreOffice Calc, a reliable way is to use `SUMPRODUCT` combined with `ISNUMBER` to filter out non‑numeric (error) cells:

```
=SUMPRODUCT(--ISNUMBER(C2:C13), C2:C13)
```

This formula will sum only the numeric values in C2:C13 and skip any `#NUM!` errors. We will replace the existing formula in C14 with this new formula, save the workbook to the output directory, run `recalculate` to evaluate formulas, reload the file with `data_only=True`, and print the resulting value in C14 to verify it computed correctly.
